docs.abstract: Market volatility is normal. Don’t fret. This advice from professionals could help prevent a volatile ride from derailing your financial planning.
docs.snippet: Market volatility is normal. Don’t fret. This advice from professionals could help prevent a volatile ride from derailing your financial planning.
docs.lead_paragraph: The stock market has been shaken by turbulence in the last few weeks, something it hasn’t experienced in a few years.

headline.main: 5 Tips to Weather a Turbulent Stock Market
headline.print_headline: Five Tips to Ride Out a Wildly Swinging Stock Market

docs.abstract: The two retailers, responding to the school shooting in Florida, tightened their sales policies. Dick’s Sporting Goods said it would also stop selling assault-style rifles.
docs.snippet: The two retailers, responding to the school shooting in Florida, tightened their sales policies. Dick’s Sporting Goods said it would also stop selling assault-style rifles.
docs.lead_paragraph: Two of the nation’s leading gun sellers, Walmart and Dick’s Sporting Goods, took steps on Wednesday to limit their sales of firearms, thrusting themselves into the middle of the polarizing national debate over gun control.

headline.main: Walmart and Dick’s Raise Minimum Age for Gun Buyers to 21
headline.print_headline: Walmart and Dick’s Sporting Goods Tighten Rules on the Guns They Sell

byline.original: By Julie Creswell and Michael Corkery

docs.abstract: The tech giants singled out booming results from their devices in their quarterly financial results.
docs.snippet: The tech giants singled out booming results from their devices in their quarterly financial results.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — For Apple and Amazon, the holidays are the time to shine, the period when shoppers have the greatest appetite to buy their devices and, in Amazon’s case, anything else that can be stuffed into a box and delivered to homes.

headline.main: Amazon and Apple Gush Over Holiday Sales
headline.print_headline: Amazon and Apple Holiday Sales Yield a Happy New Year

byline.original: By Nick Wingfield and Brian X. Chen

docs.abstract: Disney is pursuing new growth by buying most of 21st Century Fox, building two streaming services and expanding its theme parks.
docs.snippet: Disney is pursuing new growth by buying most of 21st Century Fox, building two streaming services and expanding its theme parks.

headline.main: Disney Reports Mixed Earnings and a Full Project Pipeline
headline.print_headline: For Disney, Pursuing Stronger Growth but Taking Some Punches Along the Way

docs.abstract: The Trump administration said it would impose steep tariffs on imports, the first major step by the administration to erect the kind of barriers the president frequently threatened.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration said it would impose steep tariffs on imports, the first major step by the administration to erect the kind of barriers the president frequently threatened.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump slapped steep tariffs on imports of washing machines and solar energy cells and panels on Monday, the first major step by the administration to erect the kind of trade barriers Mr. Trump has frequently said are necessary to protect manufacturers in the United States.

headline.main: Trump Slaps Steep Tariffs on Foreign Washing Machines and Solar Products
headline.print_headline: President Imposes Steep Tariffs On Washers and Solar Products

byline.original: By Ana Swanson and Brad Plumer

docs.abstract: The Fed’s biannual policy report to Congress made little mention of the stock market’s fluctuations, but it affirmed plans to raise interest rates.
docs.snippet: The Fed’s biannual policy report to Congress made little mention of the stock market’s fluctuations, but it affirmed plans to raise interest rates.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve on Friday described recent volatility in financial markets as a brief blip and affirmed its plans to raise its benchmark interest rate in the coming months.

headline.main: As Economy Grows, Federal Reserve Frets Next Downturn
headline.print_headline: As Economy Grows, Fed Arms Itself for the Next Downturn

docs.abstract: Uber said customers’ trips on pedal-assist bikes in a San Francisco pilot program covered almost the same distance as an average car ride.
docs.snippet: Uber said customers’ trips on pedal-assist bikes in a San Francisco pilot program covered almost the same distance as an average car ride.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Uber started a pilot program in San Francisco to allow its customers to reserve “pedal-assist” electric bicycles within its ride-hailing app in January. Now, Uber says it plans to buy the company behind the bike-sharing service and bring that capability to other cities around the world.

headline.main: Uber to Buy Jump, Maker of Electric Bicycles, After Bike-Sharing Test
headline.print_headline: Uber Plans to Buy Jump, Maker of Electric Bicycles, After Bike-Sharing Test

docs.abstract: With regulatory pressure looming, Google is spending heavily for its cloud business, hardware products and A.I. assistant.
docs.snippet: With regulatory pressure looming, Google is spending heavily for its cloud business, hardware products and A.I. assistant.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Alphabet, Google’s parent company, is spending like it is beginning to prepare for life after advertising.

headline.main: Google’s Parent Company Spends Like It’s Thinking of a Future Beyond Ads
headline.print_headline: Google’s Parent, Flush With Cash, Bets on a Future Beyond Ads

docs.abstract: Mr. Khuzami, credited with reinvigorating the Securities and Exchange Commission’s enforcement division during the Obama era, will become the No. 2 federal prosecutor in Manhattan.
docs.snippet: Mr. Khuzami, credited with reinvigorating the Securities and Exchange Commission’s enforcement division during the Obama era, will become the No. 2 federal prosecutor in Manhattan.
docs.lead_paragraph: Robert S. Khuzami, who led the enforcement division of the Securities and Exchange Commission for four years during the Obama administration, was named on Friday as the deputy United States attorney in Manhattan.

headline.main: Ex-S.E.C. Official, Robert Khuzami, Joins Manhattan U.S. Attorney’s Office
headline.print_headline: Fraud Hunter  Gets Key Post  As Prosecutor  In Manhattan

docs.abstract: New Zealand has opened its skies to self-piloted electric planes financed by one of Google’s founders.
docs.snippet: New Zealand has opened its skies to self-piloted electric planes financed by one of Google’s founders.
docs.lead_paragraph: Since October, a mysterious flying object has been seen moving through the skies over the South Island of New Zealand. It looks like a cross between a small plane and a drone, with a series of small rotor blades along each wing that allow it to take off like a helicopter and then fly like a plane. To those on the ground, it has always been unclear whether there was a pilot aboard.

headline.main: Larry Page’s Flying Taxis, Now Exiting Stealth Mode
headline.print_headline: Flying Taxis, Now Exiting Stealth Mode
